        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent serious eye injury, always wear safe eye protection when you perform vehicle
                        maintenance or service.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent unexpected movement of the vehicle and possible serious personal injury or death,
                        block the wheels to prevent the vehicle from moving in both directions.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <title>BATTERY CABLE INSPECTION PROCEDURE</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect positive (red) battery cables, conduit and ground cable (black) in areas
                    indicated below:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0451001" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1 - Engine Removed for Clarity</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ground Cable</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Bolted to Frame Rail</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Inspect for Chafing in this Area</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Positive Cables</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If ANY indication of chafing or rubbing is evident, replace any affected cables and
                    continue to step 4.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If there is NO indication of chafing or rubbing, continue onto step 4.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <title>SADDLE CLAMP INSTALLATION</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install saddle clamp and strap-locks as indicated below:</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0451002" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 3554554C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. 306132C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. 3516934C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Ground Cable</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. 306132C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. Positive Cables</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Note warning below for performing this service procedure on vehicles with Caterpillar
                    engines. Continue on to perform the FINAL INSPECTION.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldital">Caterpillar Engine Warning</emph>
            </para>
            <para>&#8226; After performing this recall on vehicles with Caterpillar engines, please inspect the routing
                of the ENGINE BLOCK ground cable.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent chafing of the positive cables against the engine block ground cable (see Figure
                        3), please ensure engine block ground cable is clocked in the downward (6 o'clock) position, see
                        Figure 4.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0451003" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3 - Chafing May Occur Between Engine Block Ground and Newly Located Positive Cables
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Saddle Clamp added by this recall</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Starter Positive Cables</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Chafing may occur n this area</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Engine Block Ground Cable</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If NO rubbing or chafing is present between CAT ENGINE GROUND cable and battery cables, NO
                        re-clocking is necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>&#8226;
                <emph type="bold">If rubbing or chafing of the ENGINE GROUND cable against the Battery Cables is
                    present,
                </emph>
                rotate and tighten the new ground cable on the starter terminal so it is straight down (6 o'clock
                position) and not contacting the starter positive cables, see Figure 4.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0451004" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4 - Correct CAT (non-C15) Engine Block Ground Cable Routing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 12 o'clock</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. 3 o'clock</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Clock engine block ground cable at starter terminal in the 6 o'clock</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="6">
            <title>FINAL INSPECTION</title>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Regardless of whether or not the saddle clamp was installed, please perform this final
                        inspection on all vehicles to ensure the electrical cables are properly routed.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Please inspect the starter electrical cable routing for rubbing or chafing in the following
                        areas:
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="dash">
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to frame rail.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to FRAME ground cable.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to ENGINE BLOCK ground cable.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Cables to starter case, starter terminal studs or other starter components and
                                wiring.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Positive Cable to BATTERY ground cable.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Battery Positive Cable to FUEL FILTER housing.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>It may be necessary to loosen and/or remove a battery cable to re-orient it.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>It may also be necessary to loosen/replace routing/clipping points (p-clamps, extension clips,
                        etc.) to facilitate a no-rub condition.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>See Figures below for a representation of rub conditions that require remedied.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f0451005" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5 - Battery Cables to Frame Rail Rub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on frame rail</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5a - Battery Cables to Frame Ground Rub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on frame ground</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005b" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5b - Battery Cables to Engine Block Ground Rub</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on engine ground</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005c" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005c.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5c - Battery Cables to Starter Case, Starter Terminal Studs or Other Starter Components
                    and Wiring
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on ANYTHING!</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005d" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005d.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5d - Battery POSITIVE Cables to Battery GROUND Cables</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ensure battery cables are NOT chafing on ANYTHING!</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451005e" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451005e.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5e - Battery POSITIVE Cables Rubbing on Fuel Filter Housing (CAT Engine Shown, However
                    Condition May Also Exist on Cummins ISM)
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
